This is my favorite restaurant in the city! I have been here 3 times and they never disappoint. Today I stopped in for the New Year’s Day brunch and everything was good. The pictures are of the Flora Dora cocktail, Dulce de Leche pancakes(7-8 in.)and garden omelette. So, good!
Luxurious dining with casual attire and prices!

Friendly and helpful staff. Went there for a friend's birthday, a group of about 16 people, they separated us into four tables The fettuccine was okay as well just a little bit salty. 3 of my friends didn't seem to like the beef bourguignon, told the waiter and was able to order something else, they chose the fettuccine as well and got the liberte classic burger which they seemed to like so that was pretty good. Good service 👍🏾

I expected better. The waitress was nice, the atmosphere was nice however when ordering the seared salmon, the salmon was almost as raw as if it was swimming just before being on my plate.  Round two of the dish, it was better but it was a lot smaller filet and one less asparagus. We also asked for another round of bread and that never came. No discount on final bill for the mistakes.
Surprisingly affordable brunch in a seriously upscale environment

Avoid! This place is super overpriced. We walked in without doing any research because it looked cute. For a $16 avocado toast you would think the ingredients would be fresh but the “avocado” was just a small amount of brown paste. Coffee was also up charged and not great quality.
Lovely place!  Excellent food and great service!
Spent my birthday here, everything was perfect, I had the Boeuf bourguignon and wine, it was very good.
Delicious food and fantastic service. Great prices too for the quality of food
Excellent food!
Average at best, we experienced slow drink service and our entree’s arrived before one of our appetizers.  -escargot was great -tuna Niçoise salad was v bland -cassoulet was good
I try to find a good selection of European wines especially the French ones
Great wine list and the full range of bistro favorites. Tables very well placed

Visited for Restaurant Week Saturday and had a pleasant time.  Appetizers were very good and my wife thought her trout was one of the best seafood meals she'd ever had.  My hanger steak was not so great, however -- bland with no identifiable sauce...
Had a fantastic experience here with my kids. The food arrived quick and the customer service is just great. Prices are affordable.

Neat French cuisine off the Main Street in Georgetown which gives it a neighborhood vibe.  Overall the experience was good, and the only reason 5*’s were not achieved is because the steak was not to my liking as it could have been of better quality.  Steak tartare is a must and perfect for sharing.

Ordered delivery for Restaurant Week. Went to some lengths to setup the delivery and when I got it, the steak tartare was missing. The restaurant told me to contact UberEats and said they couldn't do anything. I would have just preferred to have a correct order than jump through more customer service hoops.
Great service, delicious food, relaxed ambience. On the pricey side but worth it!
Justin was great and food was fantastic, great outdoor and warm seating during the winter!
Wonderful staff, even better food, ambience is warm and welcoming, good music selection, kickass cocktails
Great Service and eats.
Delicious food and great table service! The French Toast was huge but incredibly good tasting. Coffee was great too. Thanks!
Love their shrimp dip

This is one of my favorite places in Georgetown.  The manager, DJ is awesome and Edwardo, the bartender is super attentive, makes amazing drinks, and the ambiance overall is superb. This is a great spot for a date even during COVID times  ;)

Wow the service, the ambiance, the professionalism! Everything hit 5 stars here. We got 3 types of cocktails and all were profoundly made by our bartender, Eduardo! The decor of this location was outstanding. Felt like I could've stumbled upon this gem in a backstreet of Paris! We ordered the nibble, shrimp gratin which was perfectly portioned and I couldn't better explain how delicious it was!  There were unfortunately two unwieldy Karen's who just could not be satisfied by all the attempts at problem solving by staff and management. They raised their voice about the timing of an order and it was clear they were the only ones upset by service as it seemed all other patrons were perfectly satisfied. Will definitely be back here!

My husband and I unexpectedly stumbled upon Brasserie Liberté while exploring  Georgetown and decided to give it a try when we both realized we were more-than-hungry after our long stroll in the neighborhood. We are both very familiar with French cuisine (born and raised in the land of baguettes and fine wines, who could beat that ?) and can definitively confirm that Brasserie Liberté is one of the best French restaurant of D.C. Both of our meals were equally delicious and the beef Bourguignon divine (comfort meal at its best !). Cannot wait to be back to try the boeuf tartare and dine inside (gorgeous !)
Great restaurant in Georgetown. Food/service very good
Very nice, upscale, contemporary ambiance.
Food was amazing as well as the staff
I’ve gone twice and the service was pretty good. Food was amazing each time. Awesome restaurant whether your on a special date or with family

Let me start with the fact that French brasserie/bistros are among my favorite restaurants and also disclose that I really enjoy classic dishes.  My wife and I have traveled several times to Paris and the countryside of France enjoying some of the best French classic dishes.  We sought out this restaurant as it was the last stop down an east-coast trip full of seafood and we were in the mood for some other-than-seafood dishes.  Based on other Google reviews, we actually didn't go with escargot or mussels as an appetizer, but instead chose the macaroni & cheese - which admittedly is absolutely delicious.  The cheese was spot on and cooked perfectly.  However, the dish in and of itself, really should be listed on the "sides" instead of the appetizers portion of the menu - we felt it was just not a suitable "appetizer" to get us going for the rest of the meal - again, delicious - just not appetizer class.  For mains - we had the BEEF BOURGUIGNON & the STEAK FRITES.  Two of the most classic/iconic bistro dishes I can think of.  The Beef Bourguignon came almost deconstructed and the pieces of beef were very large.  The flavor was decent, but the lack of broth made us feel a little wanting for the more classic version.  The Steak Frites - fries were just ok - I would bet $1 that they were absolutely not cooked in duck fat, but I could be wrong.  They just didn't taste like it and the steak had an unfamiliar reddish sauce on it that tasted more pre-prepared than not and it was just "not classic".  The meat was cooked very nicely, but the sauce and the fries just made it an ok experience.  Wine - delicious - we picked out a nice Burgundy and the service was very good.  The server was attentive.  All in all, if you're looking for a classic French Bistro/Brasserie meal, I would look elsewhere, if you're looking for a French meal with a new slant on the dishes, by all means, this is a great place.  The clientele was lively and the atmosphere very enjoyable in a terrific part of Georgetown.
Great food, good costumer service, nice atmosphere👌🏻
The beef bourguignon is phenomenal, the interior of this place is drop dead! Not to mention when you come for brunch they have a Bellini & Mimosa kit, next level!

This is my favorite French restaurant in all of DC!!! I don’t normally seek out French food even when dining out but this place has been amazing every time!! The French onion soup is the best I have ever had ANYWHERE. I’ve had French onion soup at nice places in NYC- and this is way better.  For dinner one time I got the fish with almond which was delicious!! And the second time I got the steak frites!! Also so good- although a little salty so if trying to watch your salt levels, maybe try a different dish!  The environment is so nice! I’ve only eaten inside before which is so wonderfully decorated but they do have outdoor dining which looks nice as well. They are handling the pandemic very nicely and being very safe too which I like. The servers are always so friendly and enjoy being there and the manager comes to your table too and is very kind as well.  10/10. Could not recommend more!! And I work at a fancy hotel in the area and always send our guests here too!
Delicious food. Great team work among all servers.

Now this is fine cuisine! Escargot was out of this world. Ratatouille and salmon were the best I've had. Quality ingredients used in everything. Chef Matt is superb. They also did a fabulous job accommodating for social distancing standards.
Enough calories for the next 3 weeks.... but definitely worth it 🥺

(Translated by Google) Since you arrive at the place, they are with a smile and willingness to assist you, the atmosphere is very pleasant, the music and most importantly the food, super delicious  (Original) Desde que llegas al lugar, están con una sonrisa y disposición para atenderte, el ambiente es muy agradable, la musica y lo más importante la comida, súper deliciosa
A. Mazing.
Such great place for brunch.
Love the food.
Excellent food, service, and ambiance

Wonderful brunch in Georgetown! Excellent service & delicious food. Post-pandemic, the manager came out to make sure we were happy and enjoying ourselves. I assured him, yes: the server was polite and prompt and the dish I ordered was tasty and as expected. Servers here are attentive and the chef is always coming up with something authentic and new. Try the Chilled Peach & Balsamic soup — eat your heart out, gazpacho. I must say, I’m extremely impressed that the waiter remembered me from a previous visit and that the manager (dressed to the nines with a coordinating face mask) was so concerned with the level of service his team was providing. 5 stars.
Impeccable on every level!
The food was delicious and excellent customer service. Beautiful interior and a descent amount of outside seating for cool evening dinner.
Both me and my boyfriend got food poisoning here
Great place for an intimate dinner, great food aswell
To start I loved the butter. Everything else was equally amazing. Great flavors. Great service. Will definitely be back.

Everything was absolutely amazing! It was so delicious that I ate the broth and onions in 60 seconds.  Then I took my time with the cheese and bread. Sorry for not taking a picture before I started eating.
Great selection of wines, excellent food! Nice decor!

I've been there twice already. Great restaurant with delicious food and great service. They are busy but attentive and they go out of their way to make it an exceptional experience. But the most important experience I had was last Wednesday. I went there with a group of friends and when we left, I forgot to take my birthday gift ($300 gift card) and my sweater. The next day, I left town for the weekend and didn't call the restaurant till yesterday to inquire about my items. To my surprise, the manager (Dean) told me that he has put them aside waiting to hear from me. That shows integrity... many times I have left items at restaurants and never seen them back. This shows everyone there has integrity and they care about their clients. That's why they kept my items for one week. We will go back again and again. Thank you to all of the staff.
Amazing staff and good is super delicious! They are also gluten-free friendly!

The atmosphere and service was great. We ordered snails and Brussels for appetizer and they were great. For dinner we had duck and lamb. Lamb was over cooked dry and salty and duck wasn’t that much better. We let them know about the lamb and they credited that back and gave us free Deserts which was nice from them. Overall I would go for appetizer and a drink but not full meal.
Great wine list and delicious, rich food.  Staff is warm and attentive.

Went here for restaurant week with my boyfriend. Loved the ambience and the food was outstanding. In particular, I really enjoyed the steak tartare.  Definitely plan on coming again, especially when it gets warmer as they had a really nice patio out front.
Amazing service and such a modern decor. Top notch drinks and menu is well balanced. Definitely coming back
The area we were in was really loud & noisy because there was a party, but no doors to cordon off the party room. Just curtains that didn't help. The food was excellent though.

This place is amazing! I went with a group of friends and we couldn't stop talking about how delicious the food was.My friends started with the escargots de Bourgogne and were in heaven. They loved that they were really blanced and not too salty. The french onion soup was also very delicious. Next was the chicken liver and foie gras parfait. To say my friend was literally licking the  foie gras off his knife says everything. Super smooth plus the crostinis were just perfectly toasted.  For our entrees we had the boeuf bourguignon, Steak Frites, and Steak Tartare and none of us were disappointed in anything. The beef fell apart of how tender it was when you put your fork in the boeuf bourguignon. All around great entree highly recommended by all 4 of us. The steak in the steak Frites was cooked to exactly what each of us wanted and the fries had an amazing taste. The steak tartare was really balanced with a perfect balance from the meat but a hint of acidity which was divine. Overall our whole experience here was absolutely 👌 we would do it again in a heart beat and last but not least our server, James, was very warm and very attentive even with a jam packed section due to the restaurant week buzz. Thank you to the staff and none of us would change one single thing!
Amazing atmosphere and decor. Main dish was good but could have had a little more flavor. Desert was delicious and totally recommend this place.
The food was delicious and the service was extremely friendly in a very sophisticated yet casual fashion.   We will be back!  Loved it!!!

Nice place. All the dishes ranged from good to very good. On the very good side were the French Onion Soup and tartare.  One thing I like about this place is that it embraces its American French fusion nature, rather than trying too hard a pose as pure French which some places do.  Probably a little over-priced for what it is. No "wow" dishes.
Service was friendly and very accommodating! Food was amazing! Highly recommend!
Good food, very quick.

What a pleasant surprise for Georgetown. Finally, a new restaurant worthy of the neighborhood. This place is awesome, service is great and the food is excellent. French brasseries are not uncommon in DC with the likes of Le Diplomate, Bistro du Coin and Chez Billy Sud to name a few of our go-to’s. They are each different, none of them directly compete. Brasserie Liberte seems to blend a light friendly atmosphere with an upmarket air that balances well between the formal and the casual. We came here for brunch, a small group with a child and service dog and enjoyed a fabulous experience. We were catered to perfectly on all matters including food allergies. The gluten free bread was by far the best I’ve enjoyed in a restaurant, anywhere! Great job to the team here. We will be back.

It is quite a large occupancy restaurant. The menu offers some French dishes like the steak frites, the bœuf bourguignon (wine beef stew), the Paris-Brest ( pastry filled with a nutty butter cream),etc. The wine list is pretty interesting. My husband liked his appetizer: the steak tartare, found his entry very disappointing. He thought the steak was tasteless  and the French fries chewy. His enjoyed the desert: the Paris Brest. As a French person,I was not impressed with my meal. I had the onion soup who was good but nothing exceptional. The brochet de mer (fish) had nothing to rave about. Regarding the Paris Brest, I thought the pastry was too chewy. Service was Ok. I had a hard time to talk and here my husband since we were very close to the tables on our left and right and the clients there were very loud. I am not sure if I will try again Brasserie Liberté.

Dined at liberte on monday night and was blown away! Requested the "egg" table and were sat immediately. The staff was very friendly and very helpful with recommendations for both wine and food. We had several appetizers that were all delicious but the French onion soup and poutine where my favorites. We enjoyed streak, seafood, lamb and flatbread and all picked at each others dinners. The presentation and flavors where amazing. This restaurant feels super high end but the prices are so reasonable.  We cant wait for our next trip to DC - this will definitely be on the top of our list to visit again!
Very, very nice. Excellent service, nice cocktails,  beef bougignon was great. Can't wait to try steak frites and burger,  yum. Sezarac was very good too.
I was eager to try this place since bistre français closed.  But I was disappointed I must say.  Food was just so so.  I will not be coming back
Amazing space and atmosphere.  The food was terrific.  The service was extraordinary.  The samoliere recommended an amazing wine with dinner.  Would definitely recommend for anyone.

Came here last minute on a holiday but they took care of us. Sat at hightop in bar area while dining table was made ready. Orders drinks and french onion soup. Great service!  Drink prices were reasonable! Moved to dining area ahead of schedule where we also had great service and food.  Beef was prepared perfectly. Sauce was to die for.  We will come again!

Delicious (if $$$) food in a fresh, elegant space. Particularly enjoyed the butternut squash and onion soups, the boeuf bourgignon, and the Niçoise salad. Perfect with a glass of white Côtes du Rhône in between holiday errands.
Loved this place. Dropped by for lunch. Service excellent, food very tasty, and prices not too bad for Georgetown. Place is beautiful. Highly recommend!

worst food ever... the Escargot + Foie Gras Parfait was the worst French food I ever had... escargot in swamp water from the can maybe & Foie Gras Parfait was very tart cold from the fridge in little jar... disgusting, the bartender was good decoration nice.... place smelled like rotten vegetables
Amazing place for lunch, great salmon sandwich and Onion soup! Also amazing coffee!
Really enjoyed the environment. The food was delicious!

Hakan did it again! Amazing atmosphere and very professional service! we went there as a big group but they handled the dinner very well. Orders came at the same time and we didn’t wait too long at all even though there were super busy. They also have excellent chef! We really enjoyed our food. I will definitely come back! Highly recommended, 5 starts for sure!

It has been opened for a month and the place is lively and packed, it was not a secret that would be kept for long. Best French food in DC. The Beef bourguignon was immaculate. We came here for our anniversary and loved every dish. The French onion soup's broth was delicate yet very savory and complex and the onions were sweet. We will definitely becoming back and are excited for the addition to Georgetown.

We booked a table online for Thanksgiving dinner and enjoyed our meal. Food was delicious and portions are just right. Service was pleasant and helpful all the way, and the wait time for the food was reasonable. This is probably a weird thing to say in a review, but the hand soap in the restroom had a really wonderful scent. :)

An awesome experience! I had been to the space before (when it was Morton’s Steakhouse) and they did a wonderful job transforming it. On top of the atmosphere, the food and drinks were superb (stopped by for an afterwork drink and snack). I highly recommend the Tarte Flambée. Staff was great and attentive- overall, a fresh new location in Georgetown!

We have visited this place for Thanksgiving dinner while visiting DC. Great food, very well trained staff, approachable menu and very attentive managers. I came back when visiting DC for work few days later... still great experience. Highly recommended.

Brasserie Liberté is SUCH a fabulous addition to DC’s food scene and exceeded our highest expectations! Professional and thoughtful service combined with a delicious menu made for a memorable experience. The duck entree melts in your mouth and the entire dessert menu will leave you wanting for more! Enjoy!
Really cool vibe, friendly service, fresh dishes, and good drinks. First day open seems to be going pretty smooth.
Best french brasserie in Gtown!  Excellent!
